'''''\n|-\n| '''[[Marine Wing Support Squadron 471]]''' \n| [[File:MWSS-471 insignia.jpg|50px]] \n|\n|-\n| '''[[Marine Wing Support Squadron 473]]''' \n| [[File:MWSS-473 logo.PNG|50px]] \n|\n|}\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==== [[Marine Aircraft Group 49]] ====\n[[File:MAG-49.jpg|left|150px]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- \n! Squadron Name !! Insignia !! Nickname\n|-\n| '''[[Marine Aviation Logistics Squadron 49]]''' \n| [[File:MALS-49.jpg|50px]] \n| '''''Magicians'''''\n|-\n| '''[[VMGR-452|Marine Aerial Refueler Transport Squadron 452]]''' \n| [[File:Vmgr452 insig.jpg|50px]] \n| '''''Yankees'''''\n|-\n| '''[[HMH-772|Marine Heavy Helicopter Squadron 772]]''' \n| [[File:Hmh7723.jpg|50px]] \n| '''''Hustler'''''\n|-\n| '''[[HMLA-773|Marine Light Attack Helicopter Squadron 773]]''' \n| [[File:Hmla-773.gif|50px]] \n| '''''Red Dogs'''''\n|-\n| '''[[VMM-774|Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 774]]''' \n| [[File:HMM774WILDGOOSE.jpg|50px]] \n| '''''Wild Goose'''''\n|-\n| '''[[Marine Wing Support Squadron 472]]''' \n| [[File:MWSS 472 Insignia.png|50px]] \n| '''''Dragons'''''\n|}\n{{clear}}\n\n==== [[Marine Air Control Group 48]] ====\n[[File:MACG-48 insignia.jpg|left|150px]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- \n! Squadron Name !! Insignia !! Nickname\n|-\n| '''[[Marine Tactical Air Command Squadron 48]]''' \n| [[File:MTACS48.jpg|50px]] \n|\n|-\n| '''[[Marine Air Control Squadron 24]]''' \n| [[File:Macs24.jpg|50px]] \n| '''''Earthquake'''''\n|-\n| '''[[Marine Air Support Squadron 6]]''' \n| [[File:MASS 6 unit logo.jpg|50px]] \n| '''''Lighthouse'''''\n|-\n| '''[[Marine Wing Communications Squadron 48]]''' \n| [[File:MWCS-48.png|50px]] \n| '''''Roar'''''\n|}\n{{clear}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Marine Air-Ground Task Force]]\n* [[United States Marine Corps Aviation]]\n* [[List of United States Marine Corps aircraft wings]]\n* [[List of United States Marine Corps aircraft groups]]\n* [[List of active United States Marine Corps aircraft squadrons]]\n* [[List of inactive United States Marine Corps aircraft squadrons]]\n* [[List of United States Marine Corps aviation support units]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{1stMAW}}\n{{2ndMAW}}\n{{3rdMAW}}\n{{4thMAW}}\n{{US Marine Corps navbox}}\n\n[[Category:United States Marine Corps aviation]]\n[[Category:United States Marine Corps organization]]\n", "text_old": "In the [[United States Marine Corps]], the '''aviation combat element''' or '''air combat element''' ('''ACE''') is the [[United States Marine Corps aviation|air arm]] of the [[Marine Air-Ground Task Force]] ([[Marine Air-Ground Task Force|MAGTF]]). It provides [[helicopter|rotary-wing]], [[tiltrotor]], and [[Fixed-wing aircraft|fixed-wing]] [[aircraft]], [[ground support equipment|support equipment]], pilots, maintenance personnel, as well as command and control assets to the commander.<ref>[http://hqinet001.hqmc.usmc.mil/AVN/ Marine Aviation homepage] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070806100030/http://hqinet001.hqmc.usmc.mil/AVN/ |date=2007-08-06 }}</ref> \n__TOC__\n\n==Role within the MAGTF==\nThe majority of aircraft usage within the MAGTF is for [[close air support]] or transport for the [[ground combat element]] (GCE) or [[logistics combat element]] (LCE), however, other specialized missions are available. The six main functions include: [[assault support]], [[Anti-aircraft warfare|anti-air warfare]], [[close air support|offensive air support]], [[electronic warfare]], [[Command and Control (Military)|control of aircraft and missiles]], and [[Reconnaissance|aerial reconnaissance]].<ref>{{cite news\n |title=MAWTS-1 hones warfighting edge \n |publisher=Naval Aviation News \n |url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0IAX/is_6_84/ai_94262327 \n |accessdate=2007-04-01 \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070821151111/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0IAX/is_6_84/ai_94262327 \n |archivedate=2007-08-21 \n |url-status=live \n}}</ref>\n\nThe '''aviation combat element''' (ACE), which contributes the [[air power]] to the MAGTF, includes all aircraft ([[fixed-wing aircraft|fixed wing]], [[helicopter]]s, tiltrotor, and UAV) and aviation support units. The units are organized into detachments, squadrons, groups, and wings, except for low altitude air defense units, which are organized into platoons, detachments, batteries, and battalions. These units include [[aircraft pilot|pilots]], flight officers, enlisted aircrewmen, aviation logistics (aircraft [[Maintenance, repair and operations|maintenance]], aviation electronics, aviation ordnance, and aviation supply) and Navy aviation medical and chaplain's corps personnel, as well as ground-based air defense units, and those units necessary for command and control (management and planning for manpower, intelligence, operations and training, and logistics functions), aviation command and control (tactical air command, air defense control, air support control, and air traffic control), communications, and aviation ground support (e.g., airfield services, bulk fuels/aircraft refueling, crash rescue, engineer construction and utilities support, EOD, motor transport, ground equipment supply and maintenance, local security/law enforcement, and the wing band).\n\n==Organization==\nThe size of the ACE varies in proportion to the size of the MAGTF. A [[Marine Expeditionary Force]] has a [[List of United States Marine Corps aircraft wings|Marine Aircraft Wing]] or MAW. A [[Marine Expeditionary Brigade]] holds a [[List of United States Marine Corps aircraft groups|Marine Aircraft Group]] or MAG, reinforced with a variety of aircraft squadrons and support personnel. The various [[Marine Expeditionary Unit]]s command a reinforced [[List of active United States Marine Corps aircraft squadrons|squadron]], with various types of aircraft mixed into a single unit (known as a ''composite squadron'').\nGenerally, MEF postings are permanent, while MEBs and MEUs rotate their ACE, GCE, and LCE twice annually. 1st and 3rd Marine Aircraft Wings are unique in that they are subordinate to [[III MEF]] and [[I MEF]], respectively, while all other equivalent units numerical designators match the MEF to which attached.\n{{clear}}\n\n==Hierarchy of Marine Aviation units==\n\n===<center>[[1st Marine Aircraft Wing]]</center>===\n<center> ACE of [[III Marine Expeditionary Force]]\n[[File:USMC - 1MAW.png|center|200px]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- \n! Squadron Name !! Insignia !! Nickname\n|-\n| '''[[Marine Wing Headquarters Squadron 1]]''' \n| [[File:MWHS-1 insignia 2010 v2.png|65px]] \n| '''''America's Finest'''''\n|}\n</center>\n{{clear}}\n\n==== [[Marine Aircraft Group 12]] ====\n[[File:Mag12.gif|left|150px]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- \n! Squadron Name !! Insignia !! Nickname\n|-\n| '''[[Marine Aviation Logistics Squadron 12]]''' \n| [[File:Mals12 insig.jpg|50px]] \n| '''''Marauders'''''\n|-\n| '''[[VMFA(AW)-121|Marine All Weather Fighter Attack Squadron 121]]''' \n| [[File:VMFA(AW)-121 insignia.png|50px]] \n| '''''Green Knights'''''\n|-\n| '''[[VMFA(AW)-242|Marine All Weather Fighter Attack Squadron 242]]''' \n| [[File:VMFA AW 242 insignia.png|50px]] \n| '''''Bats'''''\n|-\n|'''[[VMGR-152|Marine Aerial Refueler Transport Squadron 152]]\n| [[File:VMGR-152patchscan.jpg|50px]] \n|'''''Sumos'''''\n|-\n|'''[[MWSS-171|Marine Wing Support Squadron 171]]'''\n| [[File:Mwss171.jpg|50px]] \n|'''''The Sentinels'''''\n|}\n{{clear}}\n\n==== [[Marine Aircraft Group 24]] ====\n[[File:Mag24 insignia.jpg|left|150px]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- \n! Squadron Name !! Insignia !! Nickname\n|-\n| '''[[Marine Aviation Logistics Squadron 24]]''' \n| [[File:MALS-24 insignia.png|50px]] \n| '''''Warriors'''''\n|-\n| '''[[HMH-362|Marine Heavy Helicopter Squadron 362]]''' \n| [[File:Hmm362logo.gif|50px]] \n| '''''Ugly Angels'''''\n|-\n| '''[[HMLA-367|Marine Light Attack Helicopter Squ